data.title: What is the difference between elected and appointed?
data.meta_description: Elected means any person elected by vote in a general or special election to fill any executive, legislative or judicial office. Appointed means any person who is appointed (usually by the board or council) to fill an elective office or interim office position.
data.text: Elected means any person elected by vote in a general or special election to fill any executive, legislative or judicial office. Appointed means any person who is appointed (usually by the board or council) to fill an elective office or interim office position.
